The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning representation coefficients using a kernel-based low-rank sparse model, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The method also incorporates nonlocal similarity prior, which is a common technique in image processing and computer vision (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using self-examples extracted from the input image, which is a technique used in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves imposing low-rank constraint on sparse coding, which is a technique used in information theory (cs.IT).
